<poem>
  <phead>
    <ptitle>Sonnet 119</ptitle>
    <author>
      <first-name>William</first-name>
      <last-name>Shakespeare</last-name>
    </author>
  </phead>
  <pbody>
    <stanza>
      <line>What potions have I drunk of Siren<phoneme category="a">tears</phoneme></line>
      <line>Distilled from limbecks foul as hell<phoneme category="b">within</phoneme></line>
      <line>Applying fears to hopes and hopes to<phoneme category="a">fears</phoneme></line>
      <line>Still losing when I saw my self to<phoneme category="b">win</phoneme></line>
      <line>What wretched errors hath my heart<phoneme category="c">committed</phoneme></line>
      <line>Whilst it hath thought<phoneme category="d">never</phoneme><phoneme category="d">never</phoneme><phoneme category="d">never</phoneme><phoneme category="d">never</phoneme><phoneme category="d">never</phoneme></line>
      <line>How have mine eyes out of their spheres been<phoneme category="c">fitted</phoneme></line>
      <line>In<phoneme category="d">fever</phoneme><phoneme category="d">fever</phoneme><phoneme category="d">fever</phoneme><phoneme category="d">fever</phoneme><phoneme category="d">fever</phoneme><phoneme category="d">fever</phoneme></line>
      <line>O benefit of ill now I find<phoneme category="e">true</phoneme></line>
      <line>That better<phoneme category="f">better</phoneme><phoneme category="f">better</phoneme><phoneme category="f">better</phoneme><phoneme category="f">better</phoneme><phoneme category="f">better</phoneme><phoneme category="f">better</phoneme></line>
      <line>And ruined love when it is built<phoneme category="e">anew</phoneme></line>
      <line>Grows fairer than at first more<phoneme category="f">greater</phoneme><phoneme category="f">greater</phoneme><phoneme category="f">greater</phoneme></line>
      <line>So I return rebuked to my content</line>
      <line>And gain by ills thrice more than I have spent</line>
    </stanza>
  </pbody>
</poem>